commit.message: Test JSON pointer with empty string in dict key.

Fix tests for jsonschema > 4.17.3

jsonschema raises its own DeprecationWarnings for RefResolver usage.

Require jsonschema<=4.17.3

jsonschema 4.18.0 and later break some unit tests, and also deprecate
RefResolver.
Bug reports should include jsonschema version.
Add a test for type mismatch with default strategy.
Add debug logging to oneOf descender.
Refactor code common to array strategies.

Use absolute URI in meta data schema $ref.

This fixes a test failure with jsonschema>=4.15.0. If "id" and "$ref" are
present at the same time, "id" is ignored in Draft4Validator. Because of this
a relative URI in "$ref" will not work, since there is no base URI to apply it
to.

Closes #58.

Fix deprecated use of iter_errors with schema.

This removes a warning on jsonschema 4.
